body.p: Typical stomach pH of: pH = 1-3; pH=2.0 Calculation of proton concentration as:

parameter.name: increase of cardiac output per heartbeat [ml/min*min]
rest of body fractional tissue volume
hepatic (venous side) fractional tissue blood flow
rest of body fractional tissue blood flow
Cumulative dose due to infusion ome
Hill coefficient of pH absorption effect

body.p: Using sigmoidal rule interpolating between F_ome_pH2 and F_ome_pH6. Ensures non-negative values and capping at pH6.
pH calculation with conversion of stomach proton concentration: [mmole/l] -> [mole/l]
Irreversible transport of omeprazole from plasma in the liver.

pre.code: pp_synthesis = pp_active_degradation (with pp_active = 1 [dimensionless]) pp_synthesis_k = pp_degradation_k * pp_active pp_active = pp_synthesis_k/pp_degradation_k

body.p: Identical kinetics to degradation of active PP.
